k\in\left[1, n-1\right]
\omega^k=e^{2ki\pi/n}=e^{i\theta}
|1-\omega^k|=2\sin\frac{k\pi}{n}.
\prod_{j=1}^{n-1}(1-\omega^j)=n
2^{n-1}
\prod_{j=1}^{n-1}2\sin\frac{j\pi}{n}=n.
\prod_{j=1}^{n-1}\frac{j\pi}{n}=\frac{n}{2^{n-1}}.
